However the sums due and the sums paid were stated and a balance was struck. The Memoranda showing this balance were put down as stated here and kept till Michaelmas. If an account could not be cleared at Michaelmas the Memorandum might be attached to the Pipe Roll as in the case alluded to above, where such a note is quoted by Madox from a schedule to the Pipe Roll. In the reigns of Richard I and John the Easter views were so attached.
